title._content: William, Noel and Maureen Tunny going to school, Charters Towers, ca. 1937

description._content: Creator: Unidentified Location: Charters Towers, Queensland Description: Tunny children, descendants of the Tunny and Close families, photographed on their grandmother's property at Sandy Creek, three and half miles from Charters Towers on the Black Jack Road. From left to right, William, Noel and Maureen wearing their St. Columba's uniforms. (Description supplied with photograph.) Noel Tunny,(Joseph Noel) in the centre of the photograph was an old Collegian of Mt Carmel College, Charters Towers. He studied Civil Engineering at University of Queensland. After his graduation, he worked for Mount Isa Mines and Pioneer Concrete and later as a consulting engineer in Brisbane. Maureen (Gladys Maureen) trained as a nurse at Charters Towers Hospital and the Royal Brisbane Womens Hospital. She worked as Matron at Abergowrie College, Ingham and later at Nudgee College, Brisbane. William, left, attended St Columba's then Marist Brothers at Eagle Heights. After working in the Auditor General's Office, he practiced as a CPA in Brisbane.
